  "title": "Bunker Clerk/Cargo Officer (SS600 & TR 48, SS648:2024)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Oversee cargo operations and documentation, ensuring accuracy and compliance.</li>\n  <li>Safeguard product quality and quantity throughout the cargo handling process.</li>\n  <li>Ensure cargo loading, bunker delivery, blending operations, and overall delivery adhere to company procedures and SS648:2024 regulations.</li>\n  <li>Implement custody control procedures for onboard cargo storage and movements.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate and timely records of inventory, stock movements, and daily reports.</li>\n  <li>Promptly report customer complaints or disputes to the Operations Manager and assist in investigations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in any relevant discipline.</li>\n  <li>Certification in Basic &amp; Advanced Bunkering Practices <strong>(SS600 &amp; TR 48).</strong></li>\n  <li>Certification in Code of Practice for Bunker Mass Flow Metering <strong>(SS648:2024).</strong></li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience as a Bunker Clerk or Cargo Officer on <strong>bunker tankers.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at<strong> </strong><a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
